notes: Conditional logic via Python control flow

pipeline_summary.name: data_quality_gate
pipeline_summary.description: Implements a data quality gate for customer CSV data that ingests raw data, performs quality assessment, and conditionally routes to production or quarantine based on quality scores.

components.name: Ingest Customer CSV
components.description: Loads raw customer CSV files from the source directory and emits file metadata for downstream quality assessment.

upstream_policy.description: Root task with no upstream dependencies

components.name: Assess Data Quality
components.description: Computes completeness and validity metrics for the ingested CSV and determines routing based on a 95% quality threshold.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after successful ingestion of CSV metadata

components.name: Load High-Quality Data to Production
components.description: Writes high-quality customer records (95% score) into the production database.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when quality_check returns the 'production_load' branch decision

components.name: Quarantine Low-Quality Data
components.description: Moves CSV files failing the quality threshold to quarantine storage for further inspection.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered when quality_check returns the 'quarantine_and_alert' branch decision

components.name: Send Quality Alert Email
components.description: Sends an email to data stewards notifying them of low-quality data detection.

upstream_policy.description: Runs after the quarantine_and_alert task completes successfully

components.name: Cleanup Temporary Resources
components.description: Deletes temporary files and releases resources after either production load or alert workflow completes.

upstream_policy.description: Triggered after both the production_load and send_alert_email branches complete

description.default: Implements a data quality gate for customer CSV data that ingests raw data, performs quality assessment, and conditionally routes to production or quarantine based on quality scores.

batch_window.description: Batch window parameter name (e.g., ds, execution_date)

partitioning.description: Data partitioning strategy (e.g., daily, hourly, monthly)

depends_on_past.description: Whether execution depends on previous run success

to.description: Email recipient address for quality alerts
to.constraints: must be a valid email address

html_template.description: HTML template used for the alert email body

sources: Raw customer CSV files located at /data/raw/
sinks: Production database where highquality records are stored
Quarantine storage at /data/quarantine/ for lowquality files
Email notifications sent via SMTP to data stewards
intermediate_datasets: File metadata (path, record count) passed via XCom
